<ResourceLayout 
  name="FAQ"
  description="Answers to common questions about our services"
>
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>How long does an evaluation typically take?</h3>
  <p>
    Initial evaluations usually take 90-120 minutes depending on the type of assessment. We schedule ample time to ensure a thorough and accurate evaluation.
  </p>

  <h3>Will my insurance cover the cost?</h3>
  <p>
    Most major insurance plans cover psychological evaluations and therapy services. We recommend contacting us or your insurance company for specific coverage details.
  </p>

  <h3>How soon can I get an appointment?</h3>
  <p>
    Appointment availability varies by clinician and service type. Please check our Waitlist Times page or contact us for current availability.
  </p>

  <h3>What should I bring to my first appointment?</h3>
  <p>
    Please bring a valid photo ID, insurance card (if applicable), and any relevant medical or psychological records. We'll also send you intake forms to complete before your visit.
  </p>

  <h3>Do you offer telehealth appointments?</h3>
  <p>
    Some services are available via telehealth. Please contact us to discuss whether your specific needs can be met through virtual sessions.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I need to cancel or reschedule?</h3>
  <p>
    Please contact us at least 24 hours in advance to cancel or reschedule. Cancellations with less notice may result in a cancellation fee.
  </p>

  <h3>Are my records kept confidential?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. We maintain strict confidentiality in accordance with HIPAA and all applicable privacy laws. Your information is secure and protected.
  </p>
</ResourceLayout>
